    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-04T18:17:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-04T18:17:00-05:00" n="566"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–252: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-04T18:17:00-05:00"
                            >January 4, 1952—6:17 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 594. Re Indians in South Africa.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>We approve additional para re neutral individual <gloss target="#t_Delga1"
                            >Delga</gloss> 823 Jan 2.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>We approve Del decision 21 Dec abstain on third preambular para and
                        operative paras 2 and 3 of draft Res (<gloss target="#t_Delga1"
                            >Delga</gloss> 754 and 770 Dec 20).</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Del shld also abstain on the second preambular para in view of fact we
                        voted against para 3 of Res last year which South Africans are now charged
                        with contravening.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>In accordance position paper <gloss target="#t_SD1">SD</gloss>/A/C.1/360,
                        Del shld vote against para placing item on agenda seventh session.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>In vote on Res as whole Del authorized vote in favor as Res generally
                        similar to last year’s Res on which we voted affirmatively in plenary.
                            <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> convinced, however, Res unlikely
                        accomplish anything and there is risk that coming on top present SW African
                        situation it will make return S African Del to <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                            >GA</gloss> more difficult.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
